1. Why did you use inheritance?
Inheritance was used because all transport types are Vehicles. It allows them to share a common base class and be treated polymorphically.

2. Why did you use interfaces?
Interfaces represent capabilities such as driving, flying, and sailing. Different vehicles can implement only the abilities they support.

3. Could Helicopter inherit from both Vehicle and Airplane? Why or why not?
No. C# supports only single inheritance, so a class can inherit from only one base class.

4. Why can Helicopter implement both IFlyable and IDriveable?
Because C# allows a class to implement multiple interfaces, enabling it to have multiple capabilities.

5. If a Submarine can both sail and dive, how would you design it?
I would create an IDiveable interface and have Submarine inherit from Vehicle while implementing both ISailable and IDiveable.
